How to set a python program to start on boot:

1. Copy your .py file as well and any other needed files (ex: sound files) to /home/pi

2. Open your terminal in /home/pi and type the following:
	sudo nano .bashrc
This line will create the file .bashrc and will now be opened in the terminal.

3. At the bottom of the file enter:
	python filename.py
Save and exit the file. The the program will now automaticlly run whenever the terminal is opened.

4. Returning to the terminal, enter:
	sudo raspi-config
A GUI will now appear in the terminal.

5. Select option 3 "Boot Options" and select the following:
	B1 Desktop / CLI
	B2 Console Autologin
	Finish
Allow the system to reboot